  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Africa Against Poverty</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project broadly works in the petroleum and mining thematic areas. It specifically aims to influence the formulation of the Rights to Information Bill from a local and national level perspective, push for the development of a Minerals and Mining policy and incorporate international standards and adoption of Economic Community of West African States (ECOWAS) Mining Directive in national legal frameworks. It also advocates for contract disclosure, transparency of bidding processes and enforcement of contract terms; builds the capacity of communities to track and monitor revenues from extractive industries, prevent violation of rights and avoid other adverse socio -environmental impacts and initiates analytical work on cost -benefits of mining in Ghana to detect pros and cons from a civil society perspective. Also central to the Africa Against Poverty (AAP), is the effort to strengthen knowledge of non -state regulations such as the Dodd Frank Act, country -by -country reporting, etc., and ensure an integration of artisanal and small -scale mining in the national legislations.</narrative>
  </description>
